detailedDescription.en: Basic kata focusing on fundamental movements and stances.
Builds upon Taikyoku Sono Ichi with increased complexity.
Increased complexity with more dynamic movements.
Focuses on basic techniques and movements.
Introduces more intermediate techniques and stances.
Continues to build complexity from the previous Pinan katas.
Focuses on breathing, posture, and strength with isometric tension.
Focuses on basic kicks and their application in sequences.
Introduces additional kicks and emphasizes agility.
Focuses on combinations of various kicks with precision.
Contains more advanced movements and combinations.
The most complex of the Pinan katas, emphasizing agility and power.
Emphasizes powerful, smashing techniques and strong stances.
Focuses on precision, control, and defensive techniques.
Dedicated to hand strikes and basic blocks.
Involves breaking through the opponent's defense with powerful strikes.
Long and complex kata focusing on various techniques and fluid movements.
Similar to Gekisai Dai but with small variations in techniques and timing.
Focuses on strong stances, body conditioning, and endurance.
Emphasizes quick movements, agility, and strategic techniques.
Depicts the movements of a reclining dragon, focusing on agility and power.
Contains 18 steps, emphasizing a mix of hard and soft techniques.
